[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing HV Metadata**\n\nI've got some issues with the metadata for HV, which seems to have inconsistencies related to using glassfish and jakarta.el. There's an option to use org.glassfish.expressly, but I need to be careful about OSGi fallbacks since the legacy implementations might not work well.\n\nMaybe I should consider adding both API 4 and glassfish 4 for compatibility? There's also the possibility that I could keep the current setup and just adjust imports to avoid complications. I'll keep thinking through these different options!\n\n**Installing API for OSGi**\n\nI need to install the API jar for OSGi, which can be found using `jakarta/el/ExpressionFactory.class` as a resource. It seems like I won't need it for compile, but the test compile might require it.\n\nResourceBundleMessageInterpolator seems to complicate things since it comes from HV, but its signature doesn’t expose EL. I could potentially remove the `jakarta.el` test implementation, resolving to use `bundleLocation(\"jakarta/el/ELManager.class\")` instead. It looks like glassfish will provide the necessary API, so if it fails, tests will fail too, but I might not need to include EL directly for type resolution.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0efe6962a4923ae2016a3bc1f7ba30819690d1b473bc713b4a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqO8IFDQ9NWU0LpNZrIw1pGBeJyPLx1gYCEq5Vi-p_B8hDPWHu0mtxYFQdvc8NA2vzN-snf4FXuJr9rPmSgSXbe9h_0q7qrpQjkODdiClcvkwB3_-CMta-2J2VSTiGG61VauRZzve5xccFFc0YxUQ5TGVqebmJBeTSkv5erbfX2PThPJZDputH_hYsaF0dHRKWpfym-E1K2NfS4VeKlpFnHGTK1JOinPkgDJQnBVCpRNGFNb0kvJzmzRwAls8CHcgMt3YyQdGsItgKK-T0wrVp7svCSdNVbQGq6fQjFgyDc4MrDIN93zTt7mHR1rlRDUK88x1o_HjGx-lrSZC7k9OuCnEUs9lvjbDo9aycTRihcPbGI3awao0CEzxTJ1p2EmQfuKre45GJmji4JdjGX-Qd0NwWixCUIA9BHxPoMBqzru9Q12c3WbxY0MJuVt3t7iQPkR6guvDfQK4ymdJh7hRo0q2rEyCDROO9p3Lwa14bsWI54MBF9Mro3HyoeVqj6JoB99cpdF1-SD1g8s1